---------------------
Arch Linux Install
---------------------

-------------------------
Preparing the Hard Drive
-------------------------

1) Check the drive to install to (eg. /dev/sda)

# fdisk -l 

2) Partition the Drive

# cfdisk

>> create a 2G swap partition and set it to type 82
>> create another partition for rest and set as bootable

3) Format and set swap

# mkfs.ext4 /dev/sda2
# mkswap /dev/sda1
# swapon /dev/sda1

4) Mount the Hard Drive

# mount /dev/sda2 /mnt

----------------------------
Installing the System Files
----------------------------

1) Edit the mirrorlist

# nano /etc/pacman.d/mirrorlist

>> choose local mirror and put at top of list

2) Install base

# pacstrap -i /mnt base base-devel

3) Create FStab file

# genfstab -U /mnt > /mnt/etc/fstab

4) Chroot into system

# arch-chroot /mnt /bin/bash

5) Edit locale file

# nano /etc/locale.gen

>> uncomment en_US.UTF-8 then run these 3 things

# locale-gen
# echo LANG=en_US.UTF-8 > /etc/locale.conf
# export LANG=en_US.UTF-8

6) Create Timezone Link

# ln -s /usr/share/zoneinfo/America/Chicago > /etc/localtime

7) Set Clock

# hwclock --systohc --utc

-------------------
Setup Boot Manager
------------------- 

1) Install Boot loader

# pacman -S grub os-prober

2) Setup

# grub-install --recheck --target=i386-pc /dev/sda

3) Configure Grub

# grub-mkconfig -o /boot/grub/grub.cfg

4) Setup Hostname

# echo archlinux > /etc/hostname

5) Set password and Create RAM disk

# passwd
# mkinitcpio -p linux

6) Exit Chroot

# exit

7) Unmount partition and Shutdown

# umount -R /mnt
# shutdown

8) Setup Networking (one or another)

>> Wired 
# systemctl start dhcpcd@XXXXXX.service
# systemctl enable dhcpcd@XXXXXXXX.service

>>Wireless
# systemctl stop dhcpcd@XXXXXXX.service
# pacman -S iw wpa_supplicant dialog
# systemctl start dhcpcd@XXXXXX.service
# systemctl enable dhcpcd@XXXXXXXX.service

--------------------
Finalizing the Setup
--------------------

1) Create user

# useradd -m -G wheel,users -s /bin/bash [user]
# passwd [user]

2) Install Sudo

# pacman -S sudo

3) Give sudo powers

# EDITOR=nano visudo

>> uncomment %wheel ALL=(ALL) ALL

4) Install Bash Completion

# pacman -S bash-completion

5) Configure Repositorys

# nano /etc/pacman.conf

>> uncomment [Multilib]

6) Update

# pacman -Syu

--------------------
Install Xorg Server
--------------------

1) Install Xorg

# pacman -S xorg-server xorg-server-utils

2) Install Intel Video Driver ( if needed )

# pacman -S xf86-video-intel

3) Install Touchpad Drivers

# pacman -S xf86-input-synaptics

4) Install i3

# pacman -S i3 dmenu rxvt-unicode

5) reboot


Enjoy!
